                                                                                                <meta name="description" xml:lang="en" lang="en" content="
Citrus medica’s area of origin, like all other citrus forms, lies in South East Asia. However, Weisskopf and Fuller1 have suggested that, in contrast to other citron fruits, the citron actually originated in the westernmost area of Asia, probably in the central Himalayan foothills where it was first domesticated (fig. 1). Another unique characteristic of the citron, in comparison to other domesticated Citrus" />
                    <meta name="citation_abstract" content="
Citrus medica’s area of origin, like all other citrus forms, lies in South East Asia. However, Weisskopf and Fuller1 have suggested that, in contrast to other citron fruits, the citron actually originated in the westernmost area of Asia, probably in the central Himalayan foothills where it was first domesticated (fig. 1). Another unique characteristic of the citron, in comparison to other domesticated Citrus" />
                    <meta property="og:description" content="
Citrus medica’s area of origin, like all other citrus forms, lies in South East Asia. However, Weisskopf and Fuller1 have suggested that, in contrast to other citron fruits, the citron actually originated in the westernmost area of Asia, probably in the central Himalayan foothills where it was first domesticated (fig. 1). Another unique characteristic of the citron, in comparison to other domesticated Citrus" />
